\f2\i0 \'93I suppose we should trust the crows and follow?\'94 Arabelle asks.\
Magda shrugs, starting in the direction the crow flew towards. \'93Why they don\'92t just tell us what they want and where to go, like normal people, beats me. Does everything have to be a riddle?\'94\
Arabelle smiles. \'93I don\'92t know what you mean.\'94\
Walking through the streets of Vallaki, Arabelle thinks back to her vision. Alek, searching the burned down house; three bodies lying scorched and deformed. A tavern ripe with unhappy folk; a half-elven woman speaking to them, full of anger. \
Arabelle didn\'92t always understand her visions. They were usually fragmented, unfocused, chaotic. It was hard to tell if they were still to happen, or already had. But sometimes, very rarely, parts of them felt very clear.\
