\f2\i0 \cf2 \'93Thank you!\'94 Arabelle waved, as the crow flew away.\
Magda and Arabelle were standing in front of a burned down house, its roof and most of the second floor collapsed. Oddly, the front door was almost intact, a silver eye staring back.\
Soon enough, a tall figure with broad shoulders walked up the street, straight towards the two women.\
\'93Alek, how lucky to find you here.\'94 said Magda as the captain of the guard approached.\
\'93Very rarely anything happens because of luck in this town.\'94 Alek straightened the collar of his cloak up. He looked comfortable in his stiff dark blue guard\'92s uniform, the gold rim around his collar indicating he was in charge.\
\'93This is Arabelle. She has something she wants to tell you.\'94\
Blushing, Arabelle stepped forward and bowed, \'93Captain, we met briefly the night I arrived at the Blue Water Inn. I have been travelling with Magda and the others, wanting to help. You see, I\'85\'94 She eyed Magda, looking for encouragement.\
Magda rolled her eyes and gestured to her to keep talking.\
\'93I have visions. Sometimes.\'94 Clearing her throat and pulling herself together, Arabelle continued, \'93And I had one this morning. Of you, captain, looking through this house, finding three bodies. But there was more! I saw this tavern, the Knight\'92s Head? And there was this woman talking to a crowd there, riling them up. And her name was Mordesh.\'94 Having blurted this out, Arabelle breathed a sigh of relief.\
\'93What does an angry woman have to do with this?\'94 asked Alek.\
\'93The visions aren\'92t always clear, captain, but this one\'85 I know it\'92s connected. The townsfolk, they\'92re angry. And those silver eyes are like a bullseye, marking where to strike next. I mean, look at this house, it\'92s barely standing as it is. But the door and the eye were left intact, as a sign.\
\'93I thought it could be useful information on finding out who attacked this house. Maybe Mordesh has been organising them, leading the folks who want to strike back at those who stood with Fiona Watcher.\'94\
\'93We came to offer our help, dear. Perhaps we can find this Mordesh and persuade against violence before the situation escalates further.\'94 said Magda.\
\'93Very well. I came to have another look at the building, hoping to find more clues. Two fresh sets of eyes might be what I need. After you.\'94 Alek gestured towards the front door.\
